`src/app/page.tsx:24-34` — stats and approval fetch sequentially:

```tsx
const fetchData = async () => {
  const statsRes = await fetch('/api/admin/stats');     // 1
  const statsData = await statsRes.json();
  if (!statsData.error) setStats(statsData);
  const appRes = await fetch('/api/admin/approval');     // 2 — waits for 1
  ...
};
```

**Fix**: parallel fetch:

```tsx
const fetchData = async () => {
  const [statsRes, appRes] = await Promise.all([
    fetch('/api/admin/stats'),
    fetch('/api/admin/approval'),
  ]);
  ...
};
```

`src/app/api/auth/login/route.ts:11` — `Map<string, {...}>` never prunes stale entries. Only deleted on successful login — if 10K unique IPs hit the login endpoint, all stay in memory for 15 minutes.

**Fix**: use a TTL Map or bounded LRU. With ponytail: smallest diff is a periodic sweep:

```typescript
// ponytail: inline cleanup every 50 writes
if (loginAttempts.size > 10000) {
  const now = Date.now();
  for (const [ip, data] of loginAttempts) {
    if (now > data.resetTime) loginAttempts.delete(ip);
  }
}
```

`src/lib/theme.tsx:49-52`:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const script = document.createElement('script');
  script.innerHTML = `(function(){...})()`;
  document.head.appendChild(script);
}, []);
```

Every `ThemeProvider` mount appends an inline script to `<head>`. These accumulate. **Also:** the anti-flash script runs after React hydrates, which defeats its purpose — it should be in `layout.tsx` as a blocking `<script>` in `<head>`, not a deferred effect.

`src/app/api/admin/attendance/route.ts:30-35` — Prisma already orders by NIS asc, then JS sorts again:

```typescript
const students = await prisma.siswa.findMany({
  where: { kelasId: kelasRecord.id },
  orderBy: [{ nis: 'asc' }, { nama: 'asc' }],  // ← already sorted
});
students.sort((a, b) => { ... });                // ← redundant
```

Same in `recap/daily/route.ts:70-75`. The Prisma sort is sufficient for most cases (Prisma uses lexicographic sort which happens to work for numeric-string NIS here). If strict numeric sort is needed, drop the Prisma `orderBy` and keep only the JS sort to avoid doing it twice.

